a successful negotiation everyone wins
the objective should be agreement not
victory negotiation is something that we
do all the time not only in business but
also in our social lives this is one
area where your personality is seriously
tested and how you respond to the
situation reflects on what kind of
personality you are negotiation means
developing an ability to resolve
disputes and conflicts effective
negotiation involves a willingness to
work with other people and to reach its
solutions that everyone are comfortable
with your relationships are often shared
by how well you are able to manage and
settle the conflicts if a conflict is
managed effectively then a relationship
can be maintained if the conflict is not
handled very well the outcome may weaken
your relationship with coworkers family
and friends negotiation need not always
be between two people it may be between
several people of different groups
disagreements are bound to happen
because of difference in people's
opinion values and goals many common
situations can become sources of
disagreements the key to effective
negotiation is clear communication which
involves three important skills
understanding
speaking and listening understanding
there is no point in talking over the
subject without understanding the
required outcome a negotiation is most
effective when people are able to
clearly understand identify and discuss
the sources of disagreement speaking you
cannot have one skill work without the
other you cannot have a good
understanding without good speaking or
listening negotiation should begin with
a clear concise explanation of the
problem shared concerns rather than
individual issues should be the focus of
the negotiation the negotiation process
will be most effective when people take
time to think through what they have to
deal with listening listening is an
active process rather than passive
encouraging the other person to speak
share thoughts and feelings marinating
eye contact shows that you are
interested in understanding what he or
she has to say active listening assures
the other person that he or she is heard
accepted and respected the ability to
listen actively supports an open
negotiation the negotiation is more
successful when all sides recognize the
value of the situation participate
actively display respect consideration
and acceptance work together to develop
a solution be unconditionally
constructive approach a negotiation with
this I accept you as an equal
negotiating partner I respect your right
to differ I will be receptive some
criticize my approach as being too soft
but negotiating by these principles is a
sign of strength written by our Fisher
